Notes — Nip-and-tuck affairs have become commonplace in the Junction City-Manhattan rivarly and Friday produced another thriller. Manhattan had a chance to win in regulation, but missed a short field goal, and then again in overtime but came up inches short on fourth down. The Blue Jays then pulled out the 17-14 win on Wayne Shirley’s 27-yard field goal in overtime. CLASS 5A 
1. Mill Valley (1) 5-1

Others — Aquinas 4-2, Emporia 3-3, Goddard 3-3, Great Bend 4-2, Kapaun 4-2, Maize South 5-1, Salina Central 3-3, Salina South 3-3, Wichita Heights 4-2. 
Notes — District 3 is shaping up to be a doozy with three of the top five grouped in the four-team pod — No. 1 Mill Valley, No. 4 St. James and No. 5 Bonner Springs. All three cruised into district play with easy wins. Mill Valley and St. James open district play this week. CLASS 4A DIVISION I
